            <title><![CDATA[Millions of children learn only very little. How can the world provide a better education to the next generation?]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/better-learning</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/better-learning"/>
            <published>2022-06-01T10:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2022-06-01T10:39:32.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Max Roser</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[Research suggests that 90% of children in the world’s poorest countries cannot read by the end of primary school. What can we do to improve this?<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/better-learning" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2021/11/Screen-Shot-2021-11-27-at-13.59.53-768x461.png"/></a>]]></summary>
            </entry>
