            <title><![CDATA[What is the lifetime risk of depression?]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/depression-lifetime-risk</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/depression-lifetime-risk"/>
            <published>2022-05-18T10:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2022-05-19T10:37:56.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Saloni Dattani</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[Depression is one of the world’s most common health conditions. It’s estimated that one-in-three women and one-in-five men have an episode of major depression by the age of 65.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/depression-lifetime-risk" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2022/05/Lifetime-risk-of-depression-thumbnail-768x381.png"/></a>]]></summary>
            </entry>
